Obviously threatening the fork on e7, but the center is left ungaurded. Also, once the knight grabs the rook it is stuck in the corner. I decided that I did not mind losing my rook.

Forces the trade of bishops, eliminating a possible escape of the knight if white goes for the fork. This also improves black's position because a bad bishop is traded for a more powerful one. For white, taking on h7 opens a file and allows the rook to escape the impending fork. Bc4 is not a good option because the bishop on a6 would prevent the castle. Black would also gain a pawn and tempo after Nxd4.
